From: Paul Philippov <paul@themactep.com>
Date: Mon, 8 Jun 2026 14:30:00 +0300
Subject: [PATCH] IPU v13: clear stop/reset trigger bits before starting on T20

On T20 SoCs the IPU_TRIGGER register bits for STOP and RESET are
level-sensitive.  The ipu_start() function calls __stop_ipu() and
__reset_ipu() (which SET the respective bits), configures the IPU, and
then calls __start_ipu() (which SETS the RUN bit) -- but STOP and RESET
are never explicitly cleared.  On T31 hardware these bits are
self-clearing (edge-triggered), so the driver works by accident.  On T20
the IPU sees RUN|STOP|RESET simultaneously and hangs, timing out after
2 seconds with IPU_STATUS showing an undefined MSTATUS=3.

Fix by clearing STOP and RESET from IPU_TRIGGER before setting RUN.

Signed-off-by: Paul Philippov <paul@themactep.com>

diff --git a/drivers/video/jz_ipu/jz_ipu_v13.c b/drivers/video/jz_ipu/jz_ipu_v13.c
index abcdef1..0123456 100644
--- a/drivers/video/jz_ipu/jz_ipu_v13.c
+++ b/drivers/video/jz_ipu/jz_ipu_v13.c
@@ -790,6 +790,10 @@ static int ipu_start(struct jz_ipu *ipu, struct ipu_param *ipu_param)
 	__clear_ipu_out_end();
 	__ipu_enable_irq();
 
+	/* Clear any residual stop/reset bits before starting.
+	 * T20: level-sensitive; T31: self-clearing. */
+	reg_bit_clr(ipu, IPU_TRIGGER, IPU_STOP | IPU_RESET);
+
 	reg_write(ipu, IPU_REG_CTRL, 0xffffffff);
 
 	/* reg_bit_set(ipu, IPU_TRIGGER, 6<<6); */
